ld vector and the long axis of the filament.\nThe magnetic field strength of about 6 G is found to slightly increase with\nheight, as previously observed. The new result is the observed decrease with\nheight, of the absolute value of the angle between the magnetic field vector\nand the long axis of the filament. This result is in excellent agreement with\nprominence magnetohydrodynamical models.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 3 Apr 2019 07:48:38 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 13 May 2019 13:38:35 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Tue, 18 Jun 2019 08:24:08 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Fri, 19 Jul 2019 09:31:53 GMT"},{"version":"v5","created":"Wed, 28 Aug 2019 13:05:02 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-09-18"}
